definition.value: A dictionary covering sexological subjects or terms related to sexology.
Professional associations formed of and for sexologists.

A professional association of lawyers. Some bar associations are responsible for the regulation of the legal profession in their jurisdiction; others are professional organizations dedicated to serving their members; in many cases, they are both. In many Commonwealth jurisdictions, the bar association comprises lawyers who are qualified as barristers or advocates in particular, versus solicitors.
Estradiol taken orally in the form of a pill.
A title which describes a person or some aspect of a person.
A title that conveys esteem, courtesy, or respect for position or rank when used in addressing or referring to a person.
An honorific title which is gendered in some sense.
An honorific title related to one's occupation.
An honorific title which is feminine.
An honorific title which is masculine.
An honorific title which is gender-neutral or otherwise has no gender associated with it.
Medical journals which cover obstetric topics.
Scientific journals which cover criminological topics.
Scientific journals which cover sociological topics.
Belief that it is possible for a person to love multiple persons simultaneously.
A form of polyandry in which a set of brothers are married or otherwise involved with the same female.
A marital union in which the spouses are selected by individuals other than the couple themselves, particularly by family members such as the parents.
A marriage with arrangements or structures in place which permit one or both parties to be involved in external romantic and/or sexual relationships.
A marriage in which one or more of the parties is married without their consent or against their will.
A marriage in which one of the participating members is deceased.
The practice of marrying an elderly person exclusively for the purpose of gaining access to their estate upon their death.

A marriage contracted for reasons other than a relationship of mutual affection. Instead, such a marriage is entered into for personal gain or some other sort of strategic purpose, such as political marriage.
A male-female mixed marriage of convenience undertaken to conceal the socially stigmatized sexual orientations of one or both parties.
A marriage of convenience entered into without intending to create a real marital relationship. This is usually for the purpose of gaining an advantage from the marriage.

Definitions of sham marriage vary by jurisdiction, but are often related to immigration. The essential point in the varying definitions is whether the couple intend to live in a real marital relationship, to establish a life together.

A marriage of convenience between a legal resident of the United States of America and a person who would be ineligible for residency but for being married to the resident. The term derives from the availability of permanent resident documents ("Green cards") for spouses of legal residents in the United States, where marriage is one of the fastest and surest ways to obtain legal residence.
A form of non-monogamy in which relationships or pairings are not engaged in; or a society which does not recognize or otherwise have a form of marriage.
A loosely defined grouping of persons who practice any of various forms of swinging.
A loosely defined grouping of persons who practice any of various forms of polyamory.
Monogamy in which external sexual relations are allowed, as long as there is no exchange of bodily fluids.
Candaulism is a sexual practice or fantasy in which a man exposes his female partner, or images of her, to other people for their voyeuristic pleasure.
A family including three of more adults who live in close proximity and share responsibilities.

The harvesting of habits important for the success of the community. Closely linked to the concept of citizenship, civic virtue is often conceived as the dedication of citizens to the common welfare of their community even at the cost of their individual interests.
The quality of faithfulness or loyalty.
Engaging in sexual activities only with one's parter or partners.
A demographic parameter indicating a person's current relationship status.
Jealousy based primarily on suspected or imminent sexual and/or romantic infidelity, whether real or imagined.
A pattern of repeat behavior requiring little conscious thought.

A practice, behavior, or habit generally considered immoral, sinful, criminal, rude, taboo, depraved, or degrading in the associated society. In more minor usage, vice can refer to a fault, a negative character trait, a defect, an infirmity, or a bad or unhealthy habit.

A violation of a partner's assumed or stated contract regarding emotional and/or sexual exclusivity. Other scholars define infidelity as a violation according to the subjective feeling that one's partner has violated a set of rules or relationship norms; this violation results in feelings of jealousy, sexual jealousy, and rivalry.
A violation of a marital partner's assumed or stated contract regarding emotional and/or sexual exclusivity.
A marriage in which romantic or sexual intimacy outside the marriage is not permitted.
A relationship in which three of more persons consider themselves to be married to one another, or such a group that are all married to one another.
Groups marriages are not legally recognized in most countries.
A group marriage in which romantic or sexual intimacy outside the marriage is not permitted.
A sexual relationship, monogamous or otherwise, which is not open to additional sexual connections.
A polyamorous relationship involving two or more married couples who share the same space or cohabitate.

The idea, often held in particular cults, that once a person joins a community that are married to the other members, usually in a heteronormative sense. For instance, if a man joins the group, he becomes married to all the female members.
A lifestyle in which persons participate in sexual activity as a form on non-monogamy or otherwise open relationship pattern.
Swinging in which a group exchange partners and have sexual intercourse in non-group settings.
Swinging in which a group exchange partners and have sexual intercourse in group settings.
A relationship in which the two persons involved are part of external couples.
